main event: A student at Villa Madonna, Covington, Kentucky, reported seeing a white light in the sky at an extremely high altitude over Highland Heights, Kentucky, on March 31, 1966.
interesting points: The object appeared to have a 'jiggling' motion when viewed through binoculars.
The student first noticed the object at 10:35 AM and it was gone when he looked back at it after about 9 minutes.
The FBI Cincinnati Field Office advised that there were no complaints from or about JON O'HARA, who is mentioned in the report.
The report was furnished for information to the Commander of the OSI Detachment 301 and the Headquarters of the US Air Force (AFISTIC).
The report does not include any photographs of the observed object.
sighted object: a white light in the sky
witnesses: a student at Villa Madonna, Covington, Kentucky
